Will need new speakers over next few years, but had no plans for it this year or next.  Sounds great still.  Has new head unit for stereo.   Needs 2 new tires eventually.  Has a color matched bimini top, and an aftermarket complete boat cover.   

Mechanically sound.  Every year serviced by Bottgers marine in JC.  Last year I had them replace both batteries ($240), and they ran the stereo wiring to make sure it was good.   They also replaced the perco-switch.   Lower unit was serviced in '09.   It has a stainless steel HIGH FIVE prop.  Engine is a Alpha one, 5.7L.   I haven't looked at the hours, but can almost guarantee it's low for the age.  This boat mostly pulls a tube or skiers for a little while, then it's to the beach.   We can switch to battery one, and listen to the stereo turned up loud ALL DAY, and have no problems starting it to leave in the evening.  

Upholstery is in good condition with a few places that could use some TLC.   Overall interior in good condition.  Exterior color is burgundy.   There are a few scratches, the keel guard will need replaced eventually if you think it needs one, there is one gel coat scrape that is above the water line and not an issue other than cosmetic.  

This boat runs STRONG.  Pulls skiers, and mostly pulls a very large tube with 3 kids with absolutely NO problems.  It has been stored INSIDE most of its life.  

You will not find a more reliable, quality used boat than this one for the price.    I am selling it to upgrade to a 24' Bryant.  If I didn't need a boat for a family of 5 and some friends, I would NOT sell it, and put a little money into the interior and stereo in a few years.

title: For Sale:  Arsenal SGL31-95 5.45x39 AK74 w/ Folding Stock
postcontent:
This is a lightly used SGL31-95. The rifle is in excellent condition. I shot this rifle very little, but when I did shoot for groups, it was quite accurate, putting down 1.5"-2" groups consistently at 100 yards. If you are looking at this, it's likely that you are aware of the sanctions. That would also explain my asking price. I just searched GunBroker, and a bunch of other popular sites and could not find any of these for sale. These rifles are not very common. In fact, what I did find were a bunch of standard SGL31-68s with fixed stocks going for $1,500. This rifle has the AK100 series folding stock and that is why my price is higher. While not technically banned, these rifles are cut off from importation and there is no end in sight. For those reasons, my asking price is firm.

The rifle will ship out to you exactly as pictured. In lieu of the notched civilian stock is a more desirable, unissued Russian military non-notched stock. The rear trunnion pin for the folding stock is 5.5mm. This rifle is about as straight as an AK can get. It's pretty much perfect. The handguard retainer was modded (hardly noticeable and affects function in no way) and a new retainer will be included just in case you want to swap it out. The original Arsenal grip will be included. This is an awesome AK and the only reason I am selling it is to fund another purchase. This rifle is about as close as the average person will ever get to owning a real AK74.
